+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016DASo5sa36iHJngVJQRbYn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No checkpoint exists. Non-interactive mode detected — using Autopilot.\n\nNon-interactive mode: using Autopilot. The task is well-specified in the TASK.md — this is a reactive spreadsheet engine with a clear API. The design decisions are straightforward given the constraints. Let me quickly work through the key design questions and then move to implementation.\n\n**Design decisions (autopilot):**\n\n1. **Architecture**: Single-file vs multi-file → **Multi-file** for clarity: parser, evaluator, dependency graph, spreadsheet class. Keeps concerns separated.\n\n2. **Formula parsing**: Hand-written recursive descent parser vs library → **Hand-written recursive descent** — no external deps needed, full control, formula grammar is simple enough.\n\n3. **Dependency tracking**: Adjacency list with topological sort → **Yes** — standard approach for reactive spreadsheet. Track which cells each formula depends on, maintain a reverse mapping for propagation.\n\n4. **Reactive updates**: Eager (recompute on set) vs lazy (recompute on get) → **Eager** — recompute all dependents immediately on `set()`. Simpler mental model, matches spec behavior.\n\n5. **Circular reference detection**: DFS cycle detection during topological sort → **Yes** — detect before updating, throw error and rollback.\n\n6. **Cell reference parsing**: Regex-based → **Yes** — simple regex to parse column letters + row number.\n\nNow I'll write the design document briefly and move to TDD implementation."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1007,"cache_read_input_tokens":23051,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1007},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"sessi